      "text": "In computing, a [[stateless protocol]] is a communications protocol in which no information is retained by either sender or receiver. The sender transmits a packet to the receiver and does not expect an acknowledgment of receipt. A UDP connection-oriented session is a stateless connection because neither systems maintains information about the session during its life - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stateless_protocol wikipedia]"
